<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 93 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Landed teas met strong and active demand, particularly towards the close,
reports the Tea Brokers' Association. Best liquoring and brighter east
African teas often gained 5 to 10p and sometimes more. Mediums also realised
fully firm to dearer rates but plainer sorts were irregularly easier.
Ceylons sold readily and prices tended easier. Offshore; good general demand
with brighter teas fully firm and often dearer, but plain descriptions
attracted limited enquiry. Quotations quality 160p/kg, good medium 140p/kg,
medium 105p/kg, low medium 82p/kg. The highest price realised this week was
164p for a kenya pf. 1.
