serves the construction industry, fell by 32 per cent to Pounds 503,000
pre-tax for the year to end-March. The total dividend is cut from 2.6p to
1.25p.
Turnover of continuing operations dropped from Pounds 32.4m to Pounds 28.6m
and operating profits by 33 per cent to Pounds 783,000 as a result of
general pressure on prices and rent increases.
Earnings worked through at 1.36p (2.99p) and there is a final dividend of
0.75p.
Directors said that with low gearing - down from 48 per cent to 18 per cent
 -and a low cost base Hewetson was 'now firmly placed to grow organically
and to benefit from any opportunities that an improved economy may provide.'
Thomas Lowe Joinery, a manufacturer of staircases and other joinery
products, has been acquired from Tarmac for a maximum Pounds 110,000.
