<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Major upbeat on return of Heseltine
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RALPH ATKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE prime minister 'hopes and expects' that Mr Michael Heseltine, trade and
industry secretary, will resume his political career after he recovers from
last week's heart attack, Downing Street said, Ralph Atkins writes.
Mr John Major's optimism appeared to rule out the appointment of a
replacement at the Department of Trade and Industry. Mr Tim Sainsbury, the
industry minister, will continue to stand in for Mr Heseltine at cabinet
meetings.
However no timetable has yet been set for Mr Heseltine's return to the
political mainstream and Downing Street said it may be some while. The
expectation at Westminster is that Mr Heseltine will convalesce until the
Conservative's annual conference begins in October.
Consultants at the Harley Street clinic where Mr Heseltine is staying
yesterday also expressed confidence that he was making a good recovery. A
statement said: 'Mr Heseltine spent a quiet weekend and continues to make
good progress.' Further tests are likely be carried out on Mr Heseltine
later this week.
</TEXT>
