<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 93 / BT restricts access to pornographic phone lines
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW ADONIS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CALLERS to pornographic 0898 phonelines will soon need a personal
identification number (PIN) to listen in, British Telecommunications said
yesterday.
The Independent Committee for the Supervision of Standards of Telephone
Information Services also plans to restrict the advertising of adult
services to 'top-shelf' publications.
The measures reflect growing concern about children calling the adult lines,
often as a result of advertisements in newspapers or magazines.
Adult phone lines are produced and managed by independent operators using
lines leased from BT. Premium-rate charges are 48p a minute at peak time and
36p off-peak, of which 28p goes to the operator.
The PIN requirement will be introduced in July next year, when direct access
to all adult services on lines with the prefixes 0898, 0338 and 08364 will
be blocked.
Customers who wish to access them will be issued with a security PIN. Their
calls will be billed to their BT account, regardless of where they make the
call. It will not be possible to call the lines from public phoneboxes or
old-style dial phones without a Pounds 9.95 tone-pad, which simulates the
tones of a modern touchphone.
BT said that its market research showed that more than 90 per cent of
customers supported an opt-in for adult services. It already offers
customers the opportunity to bar premium-rate calls on their phones.
More than 700,000 calls a week are made to recorded and live adult phone
lines. One in seven of all complaints received by the ICSTIS watchdog last
year concerned such lines.
Information and entertainment services on 0891 numbers will not be affected.
</TEXT>
