<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 93 / Power chiefs take large pay rises
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES, Resources Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE CHIEF executives of National Power and PowerGen, the generating
companies, received substantial pay awards last year, according to accounts
released yesterday.
Mr John Baker, who runs National Power, had his basic pay increased from
Pounds 246,250 to Pounds 267,750. In addition he received a Pounds 64,260
performance-related bonus. Including other benefits and pensions his package
totalled Pounds 393,803, an increase of 6.2 per cent on the previous year.
Mr Baker was also granted a further 93,525 share options at 264p a share.
The annual report says that Mr Baker's bonus followed a year in which the
total return to shareholders including capital gains and dividends, was 84
per cent. National Power shares closed at 368p last night, up from 242p a
year ago.
Mr Ed Wallis of PowerGen received a 10.2 per cent rise in his basic pay to
Pounds 312,802, and his total package including benefits and pensions rose
to Pounds 362,476.
The average rise for National Power employees from January 1 was 3.95 per
cent for a 15-month period. PowerGen workers last year got a flat 5.5 per
cent increase, while for this year they have accepted a 2.5 per cent rise
plus one-off lump sums related to productivity.
