<TEXT>
GUATEMALAN President Ramiro de Leon Carpio yesterday removed General Roberto
Perussina, his hardline defence minister, after just three weeks in office
and replaced him with a moderate, writes Edward Orlebar in Guatemala City.
The new minister, General Mario Enriquez Morales, opposed the coup attempt
