by former vice-president Gustavo Espina to assume office. Gen Enriquez has
been a senior negotiator in two-year-old peace talks with left-wing
guerrillas.
Mr de Leon said he had made the move to consolidate democracy and as a sign
of his promised restructuring of the executive branch of government. The
president appears to be using his popular support - and a constituency
within the military - to affirm civilian authority over the armed forces.
