FT  28 JUN 93 / International Company News: United Industries setback
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
EXCEPTIONAL costs hit United Industries in the year ended April 3 leaving
pre-tax losses ahead from Pounds 1.54m to Pounds 3.63m.
The materials handling, springs and process machinery group saw turnover
fall from Pounds 32.3m to Pounds 29.6m, with the discontinued cutting tool
operations accounting for Pounds 2.35m (Pounds 3.94m). The operating deficit
was Pounds 556,000 (Pounds 79,000) shared by continuing businesses Pounds
295,000 (profit Pounds 191,000) and discontinued Pounds 261,000 (Pounds
270,000).
In the exceptional charges were Pounds 474,000 for reorganising the Dutch
spring company, Pounds 447,000 for redundancy and reorganisation, and Pounds
1.35m loss on sale of cutting tool div-ision.
The economies in which the group operated worsened during the second half.
In particular the Dutch operations which benefited from the strong German
market and had been relatively little affected by recession, suffered a
sudden and substantial downturn in orders.
