FT  28 JUN 93 / Observer: Bottom line
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Talk about commercial logic. Sicilian police claim the Mafia have taken
their murderous business to the ultimate conclusion by trying to corner the
market in burials.
It is alleged that in the past year a Palermo Mafia family has extorted
control over 1,000 plots in one of the city's graveyards, demanding more
than five times the standard price for them. A dozen people have been
arrested, including city hall officials.
