<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JUN 93 / People: RMC's successful German connection
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RMC, the building materials group which last year derived two thirds of its
operating profits from Germany, has promoted Stuart Walker, finance director
of the German subsidiary, to the main board. In his new position, he will
cover France, Spain and Portugal.
The largest producer of building materials in Germany, RMC has had a
presence in the country since 1954; apart from Walker and one other, the
operation is run entirely by German nationals. Bruno Baumgarten, boss of the
operation, already has a seat on the main board.
Walker, 49, has been closely involved with the expansion into east Germany,
including negotiations with the Treuhand, the agency charged with the
privatisation of east German industry. The company now has 70 ready mixed
concrete plants in the new states, making it one of the leading investors in
the east.
After 15 years living in Germany, Walker now returns to the UK. Meanwhile,
his new geographic beat, which he assumes from Peter Young, promoted to
managing director earlier this year, will already be somewhat familiar.
Walker had looked after Spain, Portugal and France for four years from 1978
when he first went over to Dusseldorf.
In 1992, turnover in Germany amounted to Pounds 1.3bn compared with Pounds
378m in France and Pounds 133m in Spain.
</TEXT>
