<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JUN 93 / Clash of the cans
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NEIL BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Ecotop, an all-steel fizzy drinks can with a novel push-button opening
system, is launched today, Neil Buckley writes. J. Sainsbury, the food
retailer, is the first UK company to use the can, developed by British Steel
Tinplate, Hoogovens of the Netherlands, and Germany's Rasselstein. It has
chosen it as packaging for Gio, a new own-brand lemon and lime drink. To
open the cans, consumers press two buttons - a smaller one to release the
pressure inside the can, then a larger one to reveal a hole for pouring. The
launch marks a new phase in the battle for supremacy between steel and
aluminium. Aluminium has come to dominate the beverage market since the
introduction of the ring-pull can in 1963.
</TEXT>
