</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MANUAL workers, white-collar staff and employees in the retail industry have
won pay rises of three times the rate of inflation, Incomes Date Services,
the pay analyst, has found.
Two thirds of recent pay rises have been between 2 per cent and 3.9 per cent
compared with 1.3 per cent inflation. One in seven rises has been more than
4 per cent.
